Prismatic Joint¶

Create a prismatic joint

Imports¶

pyb2d is imported as b2d

import b2d
import numpy as np

These imports are only needed for plotting. b2d.plot requires OpenCV to be installed!

import b2d.plot
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

prismatic joint

world = b2d.world(gravity=(0, -10))

anchor_body = world.create_static_body(
    position=(0, 0),
)


b = world.create_dynamic_body(
    position=(10, 10),
    fixtures=b2d.fixture_def(shape=b2d.polygon_shape(box=[2, 0.5]), density=1),
    linear_damping=0.0,
    angular_damping=0.0,
)
world.create_prismatic_joint(anchor_body, b, local_axis_a=(1, 1))


fig, ax, ani = b2d.plot.animate_world(world, world_margin=(20, 20))
ani
plt.show()
